2 NEVADA, JOINTLY, That a new section, designated Section 3B, be
3 added to Article 6 of the Nevada Constitution to read as follows:
4 Sec. 3B. 1. The Legislature may, to the extent money
5 is available, provide by law for the establishment of a
6 business court consisting of three judges or such greater
7 number as the Legislature may provide by law pursuant to
8 subsection 9.
9 2. If the Legislature provides by law for the
10 establishment of a business court pursuant to subsection 1,
11 the business court shall have exclusive original jurisdiction
12 to hear disputes involving shareholder rights, mergers and
13 acquisitions, fiduciary duties, receiverships involving
14 business entities and other commercial or contractual
15 disputes between business entities and any other business
16 disputes of a similar nature in which equitable or
17 declaratory relief is sought. Upon receipt of a petition, the
18 chief judge of the business court may, in his or her
19 reasonable discretion, order the transfer of a dispute
20 presented to the business court to the appropriate district
21 court if the chief judge finds that the dispute would be more
22 appropriately adjudicated in the district court.
